<HEADLINE> UAE President to Visit Oman to Boost Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 26 (Xinhua) -- President Sheikh Zayed bin
Sultan Al Nahyan of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) will visit
Oman Saturday to boost bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Oman, Zayed will hold talks with Omani
Sultan Qaboos bin Said on ways of enhancing bilateral relations
and other issues of mutual interest, the official WAM news agency
said.
</P>
<P>
The UAE and Oman are members of the regional alliance Gulf
Cooperation Council, which also includes Saudi Arabia, Kuwait,
Qatar and Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
"The visit comes as part of the keenness of the two leaders to
strengthen the flourishing bilateral relations," WAM said.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Omani sources as saying that any meeting between the
two leaders invariably leads to fruitful results in enhancing
bilateral cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
