<HEADLINE> Mozambican President Says His Visit to Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 26 (XInhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano Monday hailed his six-day visit to Portugal as
successful, saying the visit will be conducive to the speedy
implementation of the agreements signed by the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at Maputo airport upon his return from
Portugal.
</P>
<P>
The president said the neccessary tools for much closer
cooperation between the two countries have been instituted which
makes it possible for more rapid and coordinated contact between
relevant departments of the two sides.
</P>
<P>
There is much enthusiasm among Portuguese entrepreneurs to
invest in Mozambique, he added.
</P>
<P>
On the "honorable cause" bestowed to Mozambique by Portugal,
its former colonial power, Chissano said it showed international
recognition toward the efforts made by the Mozambican people in
consolidating peace, safeguarding national harmony and developing
economy. 
</P>
