<HEADLINE> S. Leonean Rebels Ready for Immediate Ceasefire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leone's rebel leader Foday
Sankoh said Monday in Lome, Togo that the rebel Revolutionary
United Front (RUF) was ready to declare an immediate ceasefire in
the country if the Freetown government would reciprocate, a report
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Following a meeting with Togolese President Gnassingbe Eyadema
in Lome, Sankoh said "we are ready for any ceasefire, be it
temporal or permanent," adding "the field commanders, if possible,
will declare a ceasefire today or tomorrow."
</P>
<P>
Sankoh who was sentenced to death for treasons and released
from prison temporally noted that he had asked Eyadema, who is
brokering peace talks between the rebels and the Tejan Kabbah
government, to convince the government to respond to any ceasefire
declared by RUF.
</P>
<P>
Omrie Golley, RUF spokesman and legal adviser, explained the
conditions for the ceasefire as reciprocal agreement of the Sierra
Leonean government and the establishment of a truce verification
mechanism.
</P>
<P>
"As soon as we get a positive response from the other side,
we'll declare a ceasefire even tonight," he added.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Sunday that reported attacks by the west
African peacekeeping force ECOMOG which supports the government
could threaten the proposed peace talks between the rebels and the
government.
</P>
<P>
The on-going consultations between Sankoh and his field
commanders in Lome, are aimed at enabling RUF to prepare its
negotiating position ahead of the proposed peace talks with the
Sierra Leonean government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
