<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Greece Sign Cooperation Agreement on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and Greece on Monday
signed a agreement on bilateral cooperation in the agricultural
sector.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Cypriot Minister of Agriculture,
Natural Resources and Environment Costas Themistocleous and his
Greek counterpart George Anomeritis, who arrived here Sunday
afternoon for a three-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, covering 35 agriculture-related issues, defines
cooperation between the two countries in the next two years.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the reporters, Themistocleous said Cyprus'
agricultural sector contributes 5.0 percent of GDP and employs
around 10 percent of Cyprus' workforce, but it is currently
declining.
</P>
<P>
Both Themistocleous and Anomeritis expressed confidence that
cooperation between the two countries in the agricultural sector
will be widened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
