<HEADLINE> Nigeria, C. African Republic to Promote Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Head of State General
Abdulsalami Abubakar and visiting Central African Republic
President Ange Felix Patasse issued a communique here on Monday on
establishing a joint commission of experts to promote mutual
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
After two-day talks, both sides agreed to extend their
military cooperation by facilitating training programs for the
Central African army.
</P>
<P>
The two African countries also signed a series of agreements on
trade, bilateral air services, investment promotion and
protection, scientific and technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders proposed to hold a summit of the Lake Chad
Basin Commission on outstanding issues facing the organization,
especially on harnessing the lake resources for the benefit of its
members countries.
</P>
<P>
President Patasse left here for home Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
