<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Urges for Peaceful Solution to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Foreign Affairs
Secretary Tobias Mapuranga Monday reaffirmed his country's calls
for a peaceful solution to the Palestinian issue.
</P>
<P>
Mapuranga said Zimbabwe was highly supportive of the
Palestinian people' s struggle for self-determination, freedom and
justice.
</P>
<P>
He said this in a speech during the launch of a Model United
Nations exercise in Harare.
</P>
<P>
"We are supportive of the current peace process which is
strongly rooted in the Oslo Accords," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We continue to urge all parties to the peace process to
strictly adhere to the letter and spirit of the Oslo Accords and
give peace a chance in that troubled area," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Model U.N. exercise was one of the initiatives being taken
by the United Nations to publicize, inform and educate Zimbabweans
on the aims and activities of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Its main objective this year was to inform and educate
participants on the work of the U.N. General Assembly. The topic
under discussion was "The Question of Palestine".
</P>
<P>
"At the end of the exercise you will have a better appreciation
of the question of Palestine and working of the General Assembly,"
Mapuranga told participants, which included Members of Parliament,
Palestine Ambassador to Zimbabwe Ali Halimeh, other members of the
diplomatic corps and students from the University of Zimbabwe.
</P>
</TEXT>
