<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Court Refuses to Grant Votes for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A Pretoria High Court Monday
 dismissed applications by two opposition parties to allow voters
who are overseas or outside their voting districts on election day
to register and vote.
</P>
<P>
The court case was filed by the New National Party and the
Federal Alliance.
</P>
<P>
Handing down the ruling, Judge Hekkie Daniels said the
Independent Electoral Commission acted fairly and treated all
South Africans equally by requiring registration of voters to take
place inside the republic.
</P>
<P>
Whether a person is registered or not was a matter entirely
within his or her own volition and no exceptions were made.
</P>
<P>
In its reaction to the court ruling, the New National Party
said it is considering an appeal to the Constitutional Court. The
Federal Alliance, however, has decided to let the matter rest.
</P>
</TEXT>
