<HEADLINE> Cyprus Joins in EU Oil Ban Against Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus supports the European
Union (EU) decision on oil embargo against Yugoslavia, said Cyprus
Foreign Minister Ioannis Kasoulides Monday.
</P>
<P>
The EU has formally adopted a decision to impose a ban on
deliveries of oil and oil products to Yugoslavia in an attempt to
squeeze fuel supplies to the Serbian armed forces in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
EU called on its 15 members, Cyprus and other candidate
countries to comply with the decision.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Kasoulides said Cyprus "will take very seriously into
account our national interests" in making its decision on the
issue.
</P>
<P>
The embargo is due to come into effect on Wednesday. 
