<HEADLINE> Over 300,000 Ugandans Die of HIV/AIDS Annually: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 300,000 Ugandans are
dying of AIDS every year, almost a doubling of the figure five
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Rubaramira Ruranga, a coordinator of the people living with the
epidemic in Uganda, said on Monday this increase in AIDS deaths to
the fact that many of the early HIV infections have developed into
full-blown AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Although the infection rate has fallen dramatically in urban
areas, that for villages is still unacceptably high with more than
20 percent.
</P>
<P>
AIDS, or "slim disease", was first noticed in a Ugandan fishing
village on Lake Victoria near the border with Tanzania in 1982.
</P>
<P>
At present about one tenth of its 20 million people are said to
be HIV positive. A total of 1.8 million people have died of this
disease since it was first discovered in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
