<HEADLINE> UN to Hold Ministerial Meeting on African Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Economic Commission
for Africa (ECA) will hold its biennial ministerial meeting on
African economy in Addis Ababa from May 6-8.
</P>
<P>
The commission said in a press release on Monday that the
conference, with the theme "the challenges of financing
development in Africa", will be attended by African finance,
economic and planning ministers.
</P>
<P>
It said the conference is being held when African economic and
social development is facing serious challenges in the recent
financial crisis in Asia and Russia.
</P>
<P>
The release said the African continent is affected by the
declining development assistance because of budgetary constraints
in donor countries and competing demands for aid from other
regions and heavy external debt service burdens for many countries
in the continent.
</P>
<P>
The conference will promote dialogs between African countries
and their development partners, it said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also discuss issues concerning "policy reforms
and aid effectiveness" and "review of the African debt situation
and domestic resource mobilization in Africa". 
</P>
