<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Meets with Arafat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Salim Ahmed Salim met with
President of the Palestinian Authority Yasser Arafat here Monday,
an OAU press release has said.
</P>
<P>
After briefing Salim on the current difficulties and obstacles
his country faced in the peace process, Arafat informed the
secretary general on the plans for the proclamation of the
Palestinian State which was to be announced at the end of the
transition period set up by the Oslo accord.
</P>
<P>
Arafat made a stop-over in Addis Ababa on his way home from an
African tour of Ghana and Nigeria on Monday morning. He also met
with Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles Zenawi on current situations
in the Middle East peace process and in the Horn of Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
