<HEADLINE> 2 Soldiers Killed in Mine Explosion in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Two soldiers of the Turkish
security forces were killed on Monday after a military vehicle
hit a mine in southeastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the mine was planted by rebels of
the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party at a road in Nusaybin town
of Mardin province and the mine exploded when the military
vehicle carrying soldiers were passing over.
</P>
<P>
Seven soldiers were also wounded in the mine explosion, said
the agency.
</P>
<P>
It added that the wounded soldiers were rushed to Mardin
State Hospital for medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a near 15-year-old war for an
independent Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey. The conflicts
have claimed over 37,000 lives since August 1984.
</P>
<P>
PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan was captured by Turkish special
agents in Kenya in mid-February and has been jailed on Imrali
Island in Marmara Sea near Turkey's western province of Bursa
for trial on charges of treason. 
</P>
</TEXT>
