<HEADLINE> France Calls on Comoran Island to Accept </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- France Monday called on the Comoran
island of Anjouan to accept the framework of a reconciliation
agreement drafted by the parties of the Indian island nation in
Antananarivo, Madagascar, recently.
</P>
<P>
According to the Antananarivo agreement, Anjouan should abandon
its unilateral declaration of independence made in August 1997,
and all the Comoran parties should create the Union of Comoran
Islands to replace the Federal Islamic Republic of the Comoros
which groups the islands of Great Comoro, Moheli and Anjouan.
</P>
<P>
The fourth island of the Comoran archipelago, Mayotte, is under
French rule.
</P>
<P>
Although the delegation of Anjouan did not sign the agreement,
it considered many elements within the agreement positive.
</P>
<P>
France, which joined the Antananarivo conference as an
observer, is ready to bring an immediate assistance to the local
population of Comoros with an aid of 20 million francs (3.3
million U.S. dollars), if the agreement is formally adopted by all
the parties, said a spokesman of the French Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
``France calls on the Comorans to seize the historic chance of
reconciliation, which will allow the international community to
accompany the development of the Federal Islamic Republic of the
Comoros,'' he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
