<HEADLINE> Romanian Journalists Condemn NATO Bombing of Serbian TV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Romania's Society of
Journalists on Monday condemned NATO strikes against the state-
run Yugoslav Radio and Television (RTS) as a serious violation of
press freedom.
</P>
<P>
"No such violent act happened in any conflict area of the
planet so far," and "it was carried out by forces belonging to a
military alliance pretending it represents civilization and
democracy," the society said in a press release.
