<HEADLINE> Robbie Fowler Banned for Six Matches for Misconduct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Liverpool striker Robbie Fowler was
banned for six matches and fined 32,000 pounds (51,200 U.S.
dollars) Friday for two misconduct charges in Birmingham.
</P>
<P>
A Football Association disciplinary panel ordered a four-match
suspension for Fowler's goal celebrations against Everton last
weekend, when he simulated snorting cocaine.
</P>
<P>
After converting a penalty, Fowler got down on all fours and,
pinching one nostril, pretended to sniff the white line to the
side of the goal.
</P>
<P>
Fowler was handed a two-game ban for a separate incident during
a game against Chelsea last month when he made crude sexual
gestures and taunts toward Graeme Le Saux.
</P>
<P>
Le Saux, who reacted to the taunts by elbowing Fowler in the
head, was banned for one match and fined. Zhe bifan 5,000 pounds
(8,000 U.S. dollars) at Season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
