<HEADLINE> French President Asks Russia to Exert Pressure on Belgrade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Monday called on his Russian counterpart Boris Yeltsin to exert
more pressure on ``the authorities of Belgrade'' and said that
Russia has a big role to play to solve the Kosovo conflict.
</P>
<P>
Chirac had a positive and substantial telephone conversation
with Yeltsin on Kosovo after he returned from Washington Monday
morning, said French presidential spokeswoman Catherine Colonna.
</P>
<P>
The French president encouraged Russia to continue to work in
favor of a political solution to the conflict, and expressed his
appreciation for the ``sincere efforts'' made by Moscow over the
past one month, she added.
</P>
<P>
``President Chirac also stressed that it is necessary to
increase the pressure on the authorities of Belgrade, which always
rejects the legitimate demands of the international community,''
said the spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin has sent Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov and former
Prime Minister Viktor Chernormyrdin to Belgrade in search of a
political solution to the Kosovo conflict, after NATO began its
air campaign one month ago. 
</P>
