<HEADLINE> UAE Urges EU to Solve Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
Monday called on the European Union (EU) to play its role in
solving the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
UAE Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Sheikh Hamdan Bin
Zayed al-Nahyan made the call in a meeting with visiting German
Foreign Ministry official Dr. Ofelli, who is in charge of
political affairs.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Sheikh Hamdan also stressed the importance
of the EU in maintaining security and stability in the Balkan
region.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the UAE's support to Kosovars, saying that they
must be able to "return to their country with firm assurances
that they will obtain their autonomy."
</P>
<P>
Dr. Ofelli briefed Sheikh Hamdan on the latest developments in
Kosovo, NATO's plan and the efforts being exerted by Germany,
which is currently holding EU presidency, to guarantee the "safety
and care of Kosovo refugees."
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo crisis, which was triggered by the conflict between
ethnic Albanian separatists and Serbs in the Serbian Republic of
Yugoslavia, has been worsening since NATO launched air strikes
against the country on March 24.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of ethnic Albanians have fled Kosovo to
neighboring countries as a result of the NATO strikes. 
</P>
