<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Ride Tech Tide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Technology stocks and new
telecommunications links kept European markets higher Monday as
traders kept a wary eye on the G7 meeting in Washington.
</P>
<P>
London's benchmark FTSE 100 index of leading shares finished 76
points higher, or 1.18 percent, at 6503.6.
</P>
<P>
The session's best level of 6522 was achieved around the same
time GEC offered to buy Fore Systems for 4.5 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"Deals amid banks, drugs and telecoms are leading the market
higher and will continue to do so," said a trader.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Xetra Dax index of leading shares closed up just over
1.5 percent, or 81 points, at 5,269. But airline Lufthansa fell 3
percent.
</P>
<P>
German magazine Der Spiegel reported the airline is losing
around 10 million marks (5.4 million U.S. dollars) daily due to
delays and rescheduling stemming from the war in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, the CAC 40 gained just over half a percent to finish
at 4,284.40 as traders remained cautious amid a dearth of
big-company news. 
</P>
</TEXT>
