<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, April 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on Tuesday sacked
First Deputy Prime Minister Vadim Gustov and appointed Interior
Minister Sergei Stepashin to fill the post.
</P>
<P>
According to Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Yakushkin, the President
announced the appointment after meeting separately with Prime
Minister Yevgeny Primakov, Vadim Gustov and Stepashin. No reason
was given for the dismissal, and Stepashin will retain his
interior portfolio. (Russia-Cabinet Reshuffle)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- Canadian scientists have cloned the world's first
triplet goats, each of which was developed from a single adult
cell and they share identical DNA, or genetic makeup, the National
Post newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The triplet kids, known as Danny, Clint, and Arnold, were born
in mid-March at a McGill University campus farm. They share a
black spot in the center of their forehead, all have black feet,
the same erect ears, as well as similar head and body shape. Their
cell structures are identical.
</P>
<P>
The three goats are Canada's first cloned livestock using
nuclear transfer, the same procedure used to produce Dolly the
sheep, the world's first cloned animal that was born in 1997 in
Scotland. (Canada-Clone-Goats)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Defense Minister Igor Dmitriyevich Sergeyev
said on Tuesday that his country will have to revise its military
theory in view of the recent adoption of a new concept of strategy
at the NATO summit in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev told a press conference that NATO's new concept has
made it imperative for Russia to review some of the principles of
the national military theory designed to defend Russia's security,
saying that the revision of the military theory will involve the
entire armed forces, including the nuclear deterrent. (Russia-
Military Theory)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on Tuesday expressed
his deep concern over NATO's air-strike campaign against
Yugoslavia and his will to safeguard the country's territorial
integrity.
</P>
<P>
In a message sent to his Yugoslav counterpart Slobodan
Milosevic on the occasion of national day of the Federal Republic
of Yugoslavia, Yeltsin said, "Russia watches with concern the
developments in your nation and is deeply worried by NATO's
bombing." (Yeltsin-Milosevic)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Demonstrators from Japanese labor unions and pro-
peace groups gathered outside the Diet (parliament) building
Tuesday to protest against the approved three bills for the
implementation of the updated Japan-U.S. defense cooperation
guidelines.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after mid-day, about 5,000 people attended an
emergency rally in Tokyo's Hibiya district, called by a national
liaison group. (Japan-Guidelines-Protest) 
</P>
</TEXT>
