<HEADLINE> Chinese Journalists Condemn NATO Bombing of Yugoslav Media (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Journalists
Association (ACJA) today strongly condemned NATO strikes against
Yugoslav media targets as a serious violation of the freedom of
the press.
</P>
<P>
"China's journalists express their great indignation over
NATO's brutal airstrikes against Yugoslav civil installations and
press organizations," an announcement by the ACJA said here today.
</P>
<P>
The International Federation of Journalists (IFJ) also accused
NATO of deliberately attacking media targets, it said.
</P>
<P>
U.S.-led NATO bombed Yugoslavia's state-run TV station on April
23 and dozens of press people and citizens were killed or injured.
On April 26, NATO airstrikes destroyed Yugoslavia's ruling-party
headquarters and several TV and radio stations in the same
Belgrade building.
</P>
<P>
"It is the right and responsibility of the Yugoslav press to
report for its nation, and send out a just, united, and peace-
demanding voice," the announcement said, and condemned U.S.-led
NATO for targeting the Yugoslav media and considering them to be
reasonable airstrike objectives.
</P>
<P>
"Is this the so-called `'freedom of the press under a new
concept and new order' NATO has flaunted?" it asked.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Journalists Condemn NATO Bombing of Yugoslav Media (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The so-called freedom of the press claimed by NATO is actually
gangster logic, as a Chinese saying goes: only allowing officials
to light fires, but banning ordinary people from lighting a lamp.
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement, it seems that only the Western
media are allowed to express its point of view, spreading word of
so-called heinous crimes committed by Yugoslavia, which are
unchecked and meant to instigate a hostile attitude within the
international community against Yugoslavia. At the same time, the
Yugoslav news media are banned from telling the truth, and
exposing lies to the world.
</P>
<P>
Does not NATO call itself a guardian of freedom of the press
and speech? Nowadays, if you are not on accord with NATO's view,
NATO regards you as the brains of military units and destroys your
media organization, your life, and freedom of the press and speech
by missiles, the protest said, noting that this is hegemonism and
power politics imposed upon Yugoslavia by U.S-led NATO.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said that Chinese news media and journalists
firmly support the important speech given by President Jiang Zemin
on Kosovo, and firmly support the solemn stance of the Chinese
government opposing NATO airstrikes against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
"We believe NATO'S wanton and indiscriminate bombing cannot
overwhelm the brave Yugoslav people, and that justice is on the
side of the Yugoslav people, and the will of the people is on the
side of the Yugoslav people," the announcement concluded.
</P>
</TEXT>
