<HEADLINE> Shanghai To Upgrade Industrial Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's most
economically vibrant city, will upgrade its industrial structure
with more emphasis on creating information, biomedical, and new
materials industries.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai mayor Xu Kuangdi made the remark at the opening of the
Shanghai meeting of the China Business Summit here today. Today's
meeting was attended by nearly 400 Chinese and overseas
businesspeople.
</P>
<P>
He said Shanghai has constructed a solid base for the auto
industry and is improving development and research facilities so
that more high-tech-intensive autos can be designed.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai also encourages restructuring of assets in the iron
and steel and petrochemical industries to create large companies
and improve their technical know-how, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Shanghai is attempting to become a paradise for
investors.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's banking and insurance companies are currently
contributing about 14 percent of the city's GDP. The city has 62
foreign banking institutions, 162 representative offices in this
sector, and 19 foreign banks have been approved to do Chinese
currency services.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Federation of Enterprises and the World Economic
Forum have sponsored the China Business Summit every year since
1981. This is the first time the conference is being held in two
cities, first in Beijing, and then in Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
