<HEADLINE> Int'l Observers Arrive in Malawi to Monitor May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A group of six international
observers has arrived in Malawi to monitor the general elections
scheduled for May 25, the Malawi News Agency (MNA) reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ted Sneed, coordinator of the international observers team was
quoted as saying that the team will be meeting election
stake-holders and visiting registration centers in almost all the
districts of the country to look at the accomplishments and
difficulties faced by the electorate and determine the freedom and
fairness of the election.
</P>
<P>
The team will initially observe the registration, nomination
and campaigning exercises till the end of registration and also
look at the voting and counting processes respectively.
</P>
<P>
The observers from the United States, Algeria, Ghana, Germany
and Portugal will on May 4 issue an interim report on the
assessment of the registration process.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the Southern African Development
Community is also to deploy observers later in the month to help
monitor the election process in Malawi. 
</P>
