<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Why Kunming Is Chosen as Site of Horti-Expo '99 (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The China '99 Kunming
International Horticultural Exposition, the first to be held in a
developing country, is around the corner. It has aroused worldwide
attention.
</P>
<P>
People may wonder why Kunming, capital of China's remote Yunnan
Province, is chosen as the site of the specialized world
exposition.
</P>
<P>
A total of 20 such expositions have been held since the first
one opened in Rotterdam, the Netherlands, in 1960. But all of
them, except the one in Osaka, Japan, were held in European and
North American countries.
</P>
<P>
China submitted an application with the Association of
International Producers of Horticulture (AIPH) in 1993 for AIPH
membership and at the same time bid for the international
horticulture exposition in 1999.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, AIPH accepted China as a member and the International
Expositions Bureau (IEB) approved China's bid for hosting the
International Horticulture Exposition in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Originally, it was decided to host the exhibition in Beijing.
But later, the central government decided to change the venue to
Kunming after inspecting Yunnan Province and viewing the favorable
natural conditions, abundant biological and tourism resources
there.
</P>
<P>
Officials from IEB and AIPH visited Kunming afterwards and
approved the constitution of the exposition. The proposal was
tabled at the 48th AIPH annual meeting in 1996 and the member
countries unanimously adopted it.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Why Kunming Is Chosen as Site of Horti-Expo '99 (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yunnan, which means "land beyond the rosy cloud" in Chinese, is
noted for its multifarious climatic and geographical conditions.
It is known as the "Kingdom of Plants" since it is home to 18,000
species of plants of higher order, or 60 percent of the flora
species in China. They include plants of the frigid zone,
temperate zone, subtropical zone and tropical zone.
</P>
<P>
It is one of the major botanical gene banks in the world, and a
leading province-level flower production base in China with an
annual output of nearly 700 million fresh-cut flowers.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan also leads the country in terms of the number, type and
coverage of natural reserves. There are now 111 natural reserves
at all levels.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan is the habitat of the people of 25 minority
nationalities. Their unique histories, cultures and customs and
conventions constitute a grand scroll painting. This, plus the
numerous natural scenes and historical sites, has made Yunnan a
popular tourist destination.
</P>
<P>
The capital Kunming is a scenic city with a wealth of
historical and cultural treasures. It is reputed as a spring city
thanks to its salubrious climatic conditions.
</P>
<P>
The coming horticultural exposition is sited at the Jindian (
Golden Palace) Scenic Area, four kilometers from the city proper.
With a forest cover of 76.7 percent in an area of 218 hectares,
the site is noted for its natural scenes and historical sites.
</P>
<P>
After inspecting the area, officials from the AIPH and IEB
agreed that this is the most ideal site for an international
horticultural exposition so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urgent: Zimbabwean President Leaves for China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
left here today for China on an official visit at the invitation
of Chinese President Jiang Zemin. 
