<HEADLINE> China's Stock Market Has Rare Opportunity to Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Zhou Zhengqing, chairman of
China's Securities Supervisory Commission, said here today that
China's stock market is presented with a rare opportunity for
development this year, and this will help solve some deep-rooted
problems in the ailing state economy.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said this year is very crucial for China's reform of state-
owned enterprises, and the stock market will play an active role
in preventing state-owned businesses from continuing to show
losses.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the sixth annual meeting of Shanghai Stock Exchange
members today, he said priority will be given to the prevention of
market risks this year, and the Securities Law will help ensure
the healthy development of the Chinese stock market.
</P>
<P>
He said China will continue to increase the number of
institutional securities investors and expand the pilot operation
of securities investment funds.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said tough measures will also be taken to prevent
securities companies from misusing their customers'reserve funds.
</P>
<P>
Chinese commercial banks will be entrusted by the CSSC to
supervise the operation of these reserve funds, and Chinese
securities companies will be granted access to the inter-banking
loaning market and the repurchasing of state bonds, he said.
</P>
