<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania to Close Down 61 Uneconomic Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Ministry of
Industry and Trade plans to close down 61 loss-making coal mines
this year, by using its own funds and those released by the World
Bank.
</P>
<P>
The closure of the mines, which prove uneconomic given the poor
quality of the extracted coal and the steep cost incurred by an
eventual re-engineering, will be followed by the ecological
reconstruction of the related zones.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian government has ruled that the ecological
reconstruction should be included in the Program of the
Restructuring of the Mining Sector, for the implementation of
which a working group of experts has been set up.
</P>
<P>
Financial support will be diverted from the 1999 state budget
to shut down 32 mines, and the World Bank will assist in the
closure of 29 others.
</P>
<P>
From 1997 to 1998, the Romanian government brought 180 mines
and quarries to a halt.
</P>
<P>
So far it has set rules for beginning the closure and
ecological reconstruction for 113 mines, with another 67 mines and
quarries slated for a later time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
