<HEADLINE> '99 World Horti-Expo Host Turns Dumping Line into "Oxygen Bar" (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two other "dumping sites", Panlongjiang River which made Wang
headache, and Daguanhe River, have been dredged. The water has
become clear and the stinking smell has gone.
</P>
<P>
"Now things are much better," said Mr. Wang, standing on the
turf where the narrow railway train used to run. "We can go out
for a walk, enjoying fresh air. There are many people doing
exercises down here in the morning and evening."
</P>
