<HEADLINE> PFA Award Top Honor for Ginola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- French soccer star David Ginola has
said a "Player of the Year" award from the Professional
Footballers' Association (PFA) in England was a bonus tantamount
to the World Cup for him.
</P>
<P>
"This trophy is my World Cup," the Tottenham Hotspur midfielder
told France's L'Equipe newspaper on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ginola, who was not selected for the French team for last
summer's World Cup in his home country, said he had given up hope
to be capped.
</P>
<P>
"I have no more hopes to be capped. Now, I have other aims: to
win trophies with my side, to get ovations when I go out of the
stadium, to mark Tottenham's history", he added.
</P>
<P>
But he admitted that missing the chance to lift the World Cup
trophy along with the French squad was a big disappointment.
</P>
<P>
"Having stayed away from this great adventure will be the
biggest disappointment of my career", Ginola said. 
</P>
