<HEADLINE> Defense Minister: Russia Forced to Revise Military Theory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian Defense Minister Igor
Dmitriyevich Sergeyev said on Tuesday that his country will have
to revise its military theory in view of the recent adoption of a
new concept of strategy at the NATO summit in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev told a press that NATO's new concept has made it
imperative for Russia to review some of the principles of the
national military theory designed to defend Russia's security,
saying that the revision of the military theory will involve the
entire armed forces, including the nuclear deterrent.
</P>
