<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1130 GMT, April 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Two NATO missiles hit the headquarters of
Yugoslavia's ruling Serbian Socialist Party (SPS) early Tuesday,
the official news agency Tanjug reported.
</P>
<P>
The bombing, the second against the 24-floor building within
one week, destroyed a transmitter used by six radio and television
stations, which was on the roof of the building. (Yugoslavia-NATO-
Bombing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesian President B.J. Habibie said Tuesday he
had set the United Nations-sponsored direct balloting in East
Timor for August 8 and asked the world body to invite six
countries to observe the event.
</P>
<P>
"Whatever the result, the Indonesian government will respect it,
" Habibie told a joint press conference with visiting Australian
Prime Minister John Howard in Denpasar, capital of Bali province.
</P>
<P>
Habibie said the result of the balloting will be reported to
the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) during its general
session on August 29, Antara news agency reported. (Indonesia-E.
Timor-Balloting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The United States will not send a peacekeeping force
to East Timor because the Indonesian Armed Forces can maintain
stability in the troubled territory, U.S. Ambassador to Indonesia
J. Stapleton Roy said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a dialogue with leaders of various groups in Dili, capital
of East Timor, Roy stressed the Indonesian armed forces'
capability to maintain peace and stability in the former
Portuguese colony, Antara news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"Instead of sending a peacekeeping force, the U.S. government
will dispatch a special team to observe the direct balloting in
East Timor," he said before leaving Dili for Denpasar, capital of
Bali province. (Indonesia-E.Timor-US)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- The construction of an oil pipeline between Iraq and
Jordan will start soon, an Iraqi weekly reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Economist weekly published on Tuesday quoted an official
source at the Oil Ministry as saying that the ministry and the
Jordanian Energy Ministry are making final preparations for
starting the construction of the pipeline.
</P>
<P>
Iraq and Jordan agreed in 1998 to construct an oil pipeline to
export northern Iraq's oil through Jordan's Red Sea port of Aqaba.
(Iraq-Jordan-Pipeline)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japan's House of Representatives, or the lower house
of the Diet (parliament), Tuesday adopted three bills to implement
the updated Japan-U.S. defense cooperation guidelines.
</P>
<P>
The move came two days before the week-long visit of Prime
Minister Keizo Obuchi to the United States, with the support of
the ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP), its coalition partner
Liberal Party (LP) and opposition New Komeito.
</P>
<P>
The three bill package authorizes Japan's military to take
various measures in the event of emergencies near Japan, to revise
the Japan-U.S. Acquisition and Cross-Servicing Agreement and to
amend the Self-Defense Forces (SDF) Law. (Japan-Guidelines)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA CITY -- Palestinian leader Yaser Arafat said here Tuesday
that he favored to declare an independent Palestinian state on May
4 this year.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting of the Palestine Liberation Organization
(PLO) Central Council, Arafat said the outcome and fate of the
Palestinian people's struggle have asked the Palestinian
leadership to declare an independent Palestinian state in the
territories on time. (Palestine-Arafat-State) 
</P>
