<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Youth to Commemorate May 4th Movement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong students and youth
will take part in various activities to commemorate the 80th
anniversary of the May 4th Movement.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 items of activities will be organized
spontaneously by youth organizations and educational circles to
mark the May 4th Movement.
</P>
<P>
The activities include mammoth gatherings, the proclamation of
a youth declaration, website introduction of the Movement, forums
and photo exhibitions, according to the Alliance of Hong Kong
Youth Groups, the Hong Kong Federation of Youth Groups, the Hong
Kong United Youth Association Ltd. and the Better Hong Kong
Foundation.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that such commemorative activities are
to be held here since Hong Kong's return to China in 1997, and
these activities will last till the end of June.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony will be held on April 30 by the Alliance of Hong
Kong Youth Groups to mark the beginning of these commemorative
activities and a youth declaration will be signed for this
occasion. Another ceremony will be held on May 2 for students and
young people who have become grown-ups, and over 1,000 students
and more than 2,000 parents and personages from various circles
will be present.
</P>
<P>
A mammoth gathering will be sponsored on May 3 by over 100
youth organizations and groups, and on May 4 various organs will
jointly sponsor forums to commemorate the Movement.
</P>
<P>
All these activities will center on the theme of better knowing
the motherland, facing up to challenges of the new millennium and
loving the motherland and Hong Kong as well.
</P>
<P>
A delegation of the All-China Youth Federation will come to
Hong Kong early in May for forums and gatherings with the youth in
Hong Kong, and more than 500 young people from Guangdong, Hong
Kong, Macao and Yunnan will take part in camp activities. Some
organizations here in Hong Kong will send young people to Beijing
and Guangdong and other places for visiting historical sites.
</P>
<P>
Pamphlets and story books will be published to commemorate the
May 4th Movement.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Federation of Youth Groups will also organize a
group of young people to visit Taiwan and brief the young people
in Taiwan on the implementation of the Basic Law since the return
of Hong Kong to China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
