<HEADLINE> Israeli President on Israeli-Chinese Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Israeli President Ezer Weizman
said here today that he is satisfied with the result of his
current China visit.
</P>
<P>
"I am delighted to be in China," he told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Weizman arrived here on Sunday for a state-visit to China at
the invitation of Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
He said that during his stay in Beijing in the past two days,
he held "fascinating" meetings with President Jiang and Premier
Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
"We concentrated on the cooperation between the two countries
and on the peace process in the Middle East," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I am very glad to say that Israel has a lot of cooperation
with China in economies, hi-tech business and agriculture," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
The president said that Israel and China have many similarities,
and he was very glad that the two nations, at the almost the same
time, gained their independence, built their countries,
strengthened their economies, educated and united their people.
</P>
<P>
Weizman also said that the Chinese side is confident in the
success of the Middle East Peace Process.
</P>
<P>
While answering a question about the discussions on the Tibet
issue in his meetings with Chinese leader, Weizman said: "I
listened, I learned and I will pass onto our government" China's
stand on the issue.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think that we have great difference on this problem,"
he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
