<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Firms Scramble for Nigeria's Privatizing Co.s </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Companies have started pouring
into Nigeria to explore the prospects of buying stakes in the
Nigerian Telecommunications Limited (NITEL) and the Mobile
Telecommunications Limited (M-Tel).
</P>
<P>
Lee Barnes, Commercial Counsellor of the U.S. Embassy in
Nigeria, said that a number of American companies had already
visited Nigeria in connection with the proposed privatization of
NITEL and M-Tel, Nigerian Tribune newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. counsellor disclosed that other companies were making
plans to visit Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
He added that there would be an upsurge in the number of such
companies willing to come to Nigeria as soon as
democratically-elected government was sworn in on May 29 this
year.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of a Information Technology Exhibition being
organized by the embassy, the U.S. diplomat said that it was
normal to be a lot of public interest in the on-going
privatization process in this west African country.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the exhibition to be held on May 4 would be the
largest since the first was held 10 years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
