<HEADLINE> Nanjing-Kuala Lumpur Route Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- An Airbus A300 passenger plane of
the Malaysian Airlines landed at the Lukou International Airport
in Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu Province, on Monday,
marking the opening of the province's first international
passenger route.
</P>
<P>
The plane returned to Kuala Lumpur, the Malaysian capital, on
the same day and the air service is scheduled for once a week.
</P>
<P>
This was the second international route launched in the
province following the opening of a cargo route between Nanjing
and Winnipeg in Canada last year.
</P>
<P>
Chartered cargo routes between Nanjing and Russia are
reportedly to be opened soon with the approval of the General
Administration of the Civil Aviation of China.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu is also expected to offer chartered cargo routes to
Thailand, the Republic of Korea and Japan within a year.  
