The benchmark Straits Times Index gained 6.77 point to end at
1,876.39 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume increased to 520.95 million units valued at
672.40 million Singapore dollars (397.87 million U.S. dollars).
Losers led gainers by 174 to 132 with 129 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Frt Links was the most heavily traded stock of the day with a
turnover of 58.65 million shares. It was followed by Dragon that
had 18.18 million units transacted. UIC was the next with 14.46
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
CenProp led gainers of the day rising up 1.00 Singapore dollars
to close at 11.00 Singapore dollars. C&AMP;C earned 75 cents to finish
at 10.20 Singapore dollars. DBS F and SIA F were each 50 cents
higher to end at 17.80 and 15.90 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, CityDev was the biggest loser of the day
retreating 30 cents to close at 11.20 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem
and NatElec came second shedding 20 cents to finish at 14.70 and
5.65 Singapore dollars respectively. Elec&AMP;E was the next falling
10 cents to finish at 3.94 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the inflow of foreign investment was significantly
less than during the last two weeks.
</P>
<P>
They noted that optimistic sentiment still dominates the market
as the result of people's strong belief of recovering regional
economies. 
</P>
