<HEADLINE> Export of Eastern Port City Grows Six Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Qingdao, a leading port city in
east China's Shandong Province, exported 2.17 billion U.S. dollars
worth of goods in the first quarter of this year, representing a
six-percent rise from last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
A multi-outlet export strategy has enjoyed good initial results
with exports to Europe, the United States and Africa growing by a
big margin.
</P>
<P>
In the amount of total exports, the ratio of high-tech and
value-added products increased significantly.
</P>
<P>
The freight volume of container vessels grew by 10 percent. Air
transport to Southeast Asian countries, Japan and the Republic of
Korea was at an all time high. More than 387,000 Chinese and
foreign passengers traveled on the said routes. And the volume of
import and export goods carried by airlines soared 37.5 percent in
the first quarter.  
