<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African Grey Parrots Face Extinction in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- An increased trade in the African
grey parrot has put the endangered birds at the brink of
extinction in Nigeria with the parrots paradise at Okodi Village
in northern Nigeria under severe threat.
</P>
<P>
According to the Environmental Rights Actions (ERA), government
efforts to protect the African grey parrot is being thwarted by a
ring of international poachers, This Day newspaper reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
ERA said "some influential Nigerians who are based mainly in
Kano and Port Harcourt sponsor the poachers who are mainly
immigrants from Ghana."
</P>
<P>
The trade in the African grey parrot persists in Nigeria
despite the nation's adoption of the Convention on International
Trade in Endangered Species (CITES) of fauna and flora to curb the
trade in endangered plants and animals.
</P>
<P>
To enforce the convention, the Nigerian government promulgated
the Endangered Species (control of international trade and
traffic) Decree in 1985.
</P>
<P>
But since then, ERA said, the government had "done little or
nothing to protect any of the endangered animal and plant species
covered by the decree."
</P>
<P>
Although the trade in endangered wildlife is almost as
lucrative as trade in hard drugs, criminals find the former more
attractive because the penalty for poaching endangered animals is
said to be far less than those for drug related offences.
</P>
<P>
The African parrot is a grey-colored bird with a scarlet tail
whose habitat is limited mainly to the swamps and mangroves of the
lowland forest of equatorial African countries like Nigeria,
Ghana, Sierra Leone, Guinea, Liberia and Cote d'Ivoire.
</P>
<P>
Fondly called "brain and beauty", the bird is sought all over
the world as pet due to its beauty, intelligence and peculiar
ability to speak and whistle like a human. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
