<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Promote Farm Produce Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- China's leading industrial and
commercial city of Shanghai will take a series of measures to
enhance its farm produce exports.
</P>
<P>
It will mainly improve the product mix, with emphasis on
increasing production of specialties and environment-friendly food.
</P>
<P>
Advanced quality standards will be introduced from abroad for
agricultural production on the outskirts of the city, so as to
raise the quality of local products up to international levels.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai will also encourage the non-public sector to
participate in exporting farm produce.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Mayor Feng Guoqin referred to the move as part of the
city's plan to open its agricultural sector in an all-round way.
</P>
<P>
The city's annual export of agricultural products is only about
100 million U.S. dollars, accounting for less than 10 percent of
the city's total agricultural output.
</P>
<P>
That is not in proportion to the level of Shanghai's
agricultural development, Feng said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
