<HEADLINE> China Concerned over Japan's Approval of Military Cooperation Act (Details Added) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- China is deeply concerned about
the approval of relevant acts of the New Japan-U.S. Defense
Guidelines by the Lower House of the Japanese Diet, Foreign
Ministry Spokesman Sun Yuxi said at a regular press conference
here today.
</P>
<P>
In disregard of the strong concerns from China and other
surrounding countries, Japan passed relevant acts, which are aimed
to strengthen military cooperation between Japan and the United
States, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
At a time when both the regional and international situations
are moving towards relaxation, such a move goes against the
historical trend, and will have a new unstable and negative impact
on regional security, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the Chinese Government has time and
again expounded its position on this issue to the Japanese side
through various channels, and the Japanese side has also in turn
made a series of commitments in this regard.
</P>
<P>
China demands that Japan strictly abide by its commitments by
taking practical actions, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Japan will properly handle issues
concerning Taiwan by following the principles set forth in the
China-Japan Joint Declaration and the China-Japan Peace and
Friendship Treaty, and that it will not do anything that will
interfere in China's internal affairs and damage bilateral ties.
</P>
</TEXT>
