<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Trade Mission Arrives at Clark for Investment Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A trade mission of 17 officials
and representatives of Silicon Valley firms in the United States
has been discussing with Clark authorities trade and investment
projects in software and hardware, urban waste management and
housing projects.
</P>
<P>
Philippines News Agency (PNA) said Tuesday the U.S. mission
headed by Filipino-American Mayor Henry Manayan of Milpitas also
held talks with Clark Development Corporation (CDC) officials
headed by Rufo Colayco on the operation and management of
high-tech industrial estates.
</P>
<P>
Clark is a former U.S. military base in the Philippines while
Milpitas is one of the satellite cities in Silicon Valley which
hosts Intel, Hewlett-Packard, Sunb Micro Systems and other
computer giants.
</P>
<P>
According to PNA, Colayco cited the mission's importance not
only in the promotion of the Clark Special Economic Zone but also
in bringing to the Philippines opportunities for tech-transfer and
improvement of direct trade relations with Silicon Valley firms.
</P>
<P>
The trade mission from the famous California electronic capital
is the third business delegation brought to the Clark zone by
Mayor Manayan and Silicon Valley Marketing Management (SVMM), an
organization of Filipino-American businessmen based in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The first two trade missions have resulted in the signing of
business ventures for the Clark zone such as the high-end computer
animation and film colorization project by Tri-Advance Systems
from Milpitas and Hollywood.
</P>
<P>
Manayan said they "found Clark (zone) to be very conducive to
high-tech industrial projects."
</P>
<P>
Members of the trade mission said they were looking for a
partner in the Philippines in manufacturing and marketing for the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) region catalytic
converters for motor vehicles, a device used in reducing vehicle
emission and increasing fuel efficiency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
