<HEADLINE> China Hopes for Proper settlement of Sino-Indian Border Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua)-- China expressed the hope today
that Sino-Indian border issue will be properly settled through
friendly negotiations, and on the basis of mutual respect.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi made the remark in
reply to a related question at a press conference this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He said that the related issue is left over from history, and
that both sides have conducted 11 rounds of negotiations on the
issue.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Premier Qian Qichen and Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan met with K. Raghunath, foreign secretary of India, Monday.
</P>
<P>
Raghunath arrived in Beijing Sunday to attend the 11th meeting
of the China-India joint working group on border issues.
