<HEADLINE> Asian Industrial Technology Congress Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Industrial Technology
Congress (AITC) '99 opened here Tuesday, showcasing the latest
industrial technologies, products and services.
</P>
<P>
The congress encourages the exchange and interaction of
international industrialists by presenting over 200 new
technologies to suppliers, industrialists, entrepreneurs and
researchers from 15 countries and regions in the Asia Pacific
region, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day congress, organized by the Hong Kong
Polytechnic University, three symposia will be held to cover major
presentations on such areas as electronics, bio-technology,
chemical industry, health care, construction material and
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's Secretary for Trade and Industry Chau Tak Hay said
at the opening ceremony that the Special Administrative Region
government is "fully aware of the challenges and opportunities of
the technology age."
</P>
<P>
Hosting the congress for a second time, Chau said, Hong Kong
aims to encourage technological innovation and facilitate the
application of technologies.
</P>
<P>
According to the recommendations made by the Commission on
Innovation and Technology, which was appointed by Chief Executive
Tung Chee Hwa in 1998, the SAR government is now working out the
details for setting up a 5 billion-HK-dollar (641 million U.S.
dollar) Innovation and Technology Fund to finance projects seeking
industrial and technological upgrading in Hong Kong, Chau said.
</P>
<P>
Chau said he is "encouraged to see that this year's congress
has successfully attracted participants from so many economies and
such diverse backgrounds." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
