<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Island Province Yields High Agricultural Returns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Investing in tropical agriculture
in China's southernmost island province of Hainan has yielded high
returns.
</P>
<P>
A survey made by the provincial People's Congress standing
committee shows that the return rate is as high as one for five.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector assimilated a total of 2 billion yuan
between 1994 and 1997, which was mainly used for improving
agricultural facilities and the distribution system and spreading
scientific farming.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the agricultural value added increased by 193
percent from 5.4 billion yuan to 15.9 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The yield of vegetables and fruit recorded the highest growth
at a rate of 96.7 percent and 154 percent, respectively, to 2.11
million tons and 391,000 tons in 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
