<HEADLINE> Soybean Milk Becomes One of Chinese's Major Healthy Drinks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A survey covering 12 major
Chinese cities indicates that 55.3 percent of their residents have
consumed milky drinks in the past one year, 25.5 percent of whom
have had soybean milk.
</P>
<P>
Health experts say that soybean milk has become one of Chinese
people's major healthy drinks, together with fresh milk and yogurt
</P>
<P>
Soybean milk was introduced into China in the early 1980s and
attracted more and more Chinese consumers.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that soybean was accepted so quickly by Chinese
people because of two factors: firstly most Chinese people hadn't
formed a habit of drinking milk and the other is that Chinese
people have a tradition of drinking soybean juice.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China's current annual soybean milk
production has reached over 40,000 tons, with the Weiwei Group in
east China's Jiangsu Province, Liyuan Group in east China's
Shandong Province and the Heilongjiang Soybean Food Company as the
top three producers.
</P>
<P>
China's soybean milk producer are also engaged in offering new
products. For example, the Shandong Liyuan Group took the lead in
adding some other nutritional elements, such as fruit and
vegetable juice to their soybean milk.
</P>
<P>
And the group provided new products in 1998 especially for
infants and patients suffering a lack of calcium and affected by
diabetes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
