<HEADLINE> East China Province Reports Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province, a
major economic powerhouse of the country, has achieved 155.4
billion yuan in gross domestic product for the first quarter of
the year, up 10.4 percent from the 1998 period.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturing sector registered a 13.4 percent growth, with
combined added value of its major manufacturers topping 45.6
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The efficiency of the manufacturing sector has greatly improved,
with total pretax profits for the first two months increasing 52.8
percent year on year to reach 6.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Exports of the province continued to grow by 13.8 percent to 3.
46 billion U.S. dollars during the quarter; of that, 63.8 percent
was accomplished by overseas funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
About 16.4 billion yuan was injected into fixed assets, an
increase of 20 percent, further stimulating market demand.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show the quarter's retail sales of consumer
goods jumped 7.6 percent to hit 60 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
