<HEADLINE> Kenya Airways Carries 22% More Passengers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Kenya Airways' (KA)
passengers carriage for 1998/99 financial year ending last month
soared to over one million, an increase of 22 percent the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
The total passenger carriage for the year rose to 1.05 million,
compared with 859,000 passengers airlifted during the previous
year, according to KA commercial director George Kivindyo.
</P>
<P>
Kivindyo revealed this during a special presentation to the
airline's millionth passenger Martin Wahome, a human resources
manager with Block Hotel in Nairobi, local media reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kivindyo attributed the growth of passenger volume to KA's
recent capacity and route expansion, which had introduce new
services as well as frequency increase on its existing service
network.
</P>
<P>
With the acquisition of two new air bus aircraft in March, KA
currently operates a fleet of 10 all-jet aircraft including
Airbus A310-300 and Boeing 737 jets.
</P>
<P>
Kivindyo said based on the airline's fleet and network
expansion, there has been a dramatic increase in city pair
connections from 270 to 750 per week.
</P>
<P>
In its summer schedules, KA has introduced new services to
Abidjan,  capital of Cote d'lvoire, while providing daily,
day-light and night flights to Amsterdam, the Netherlands.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
