<HEADLINE> Guangxi Launches Green Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- An eight-month "green campaign"
has been launched here among millions of young people in China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The campaign is aimed at enhancing the environmental awareness
of young people and the protection of the local environment,
particularly focusing on protecting rivers to greet the new
century.
</P>
<P>
During the next eight months, millions of young people will
participate in activities, such as the protection of the Yi River,
green summer camps and environment forums.
</P>
<P>
Three thousand of young people planted trees, and gave a
facelift to the main street here at the weekend while hundreds of
people attended an environmental forum.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere in the region, various activities have also been
held to promote the environmental campaign. 
</P>
