<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Conference on Innovative Medicine Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- An international conference to
discuss innovative therapies based on the integration of modern
and traditional medicines opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The first World Conference on Innovative Integrated Medicine
provides an opportunity for domestic and overseas experts to
exchange and discuss the latest discoveries, new technology and
new findings of medical research in fields like cardio and
cerebral vascular illnesses, cancer, infectious diseases and
genetic diseases, according to Qian Xinzhong, the conference
chairman.
</P>
<P>
"It is important for China, which has a thousand-year-long
history of using traditional medicines, to hold such an event as
medical treatment is entering a new era with the rapid growth of
life sciences," Qian said at the opening ceremony of the event,
which has been organized by the Chinese Health Care Association on
Aging.
</P>
<P>
Qian stressed the importance of geriatric research, saying that
as human life expectancy is being prolonged, any new research
findings to better the health care of older persons should be a
key part of medical innovation.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 Chinese scientists and their counterparts from
the United States, Canada, Australia, Japan, India and other
countries will hold seminars on genetic engineering, new therapies,
geriatrics, rehabilitation research, and the modernization of
traditional Chinese medicine.
</P>
<P>
The three-day event would invite a group of experts to deliver
keynote speeches on topics such as clinical research of diabetes
and the Alzheimer's disease, the treatment of ischemic strokes by
using traditional Chinese medicine, and Internet-based development
of medical science in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
