<HEADLINE> Marbury's 20 Assists Sunday Tops in NBA This Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- New Jersey's Stephon Marbury
had a game to remember Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
He scored 26 points and recorded an NBA season-high 20 assists
in New Jersey's 120-98 victory over Central Division-leading
Indiana.
</P>
<P>
"It was probably my best NBA game," Marbury said after the
game. "Everybody played well, everybody shot well. I was seeing
the court and guys were going to open spaces."
</P>
<P>
The 20 assists, a career-high for Marbury, surpassed the 19
assists by Phoenix's Jason Kidd earlier this season. It was the
most in the NBA since Rod Strickland of Washington also notched 20
assists on February 10, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The all-time NBA record for assists in a single game is 30 by
Orlando's Scott Skiles, which he recorded against Denver on
December 30, 1990. Skiles is currently an assistant for the
Phoenix Suns. 
