<HEADLINE> NATO Bombs Yugoslavia's Ruling Party Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Two NATO missiles hit the
headquarters of Yugoslavia's ruling Serbian Socialist Party (SPS)
early Tuesday, the official news agency Tanjug reported.
</P>
<P>
The bombing, the second against the 24-floor building within
one week, destroyed a transmitter used by six radio and television
stations, which was on the roof of the building.
</P>
<P>
Situated on the left bank of the Sava river in Belgrade, the
building houses the headquarters of the SPS as well as those of
more than 20 companies.
</P>
<P>
