<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chang Wins First Round in Atlanta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Two-time champion Michael
Chang beat Italy's Gianluca Pozzi in the opening round of the 350,
000 U.S. dollars ATP Challenge here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chang, who had won only two of his past eight matches, improved
to 7-0 lifetime over Pozzi with a 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed Chang advanced to a second-round matchup with
either Australia's Todd Woodbridge or qualifier Stefan Koubek.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Jason Stoltenberg of Australia ousted American wild
card Paul Goldstein 6-4, 6-1, to set up a second round clash with
compatriot Mark Woodforde, a 2-6, 6-3, 6-4 winner over Aussie
Lleyton Hewitt.
</P>
<P>
