<HEADLINE> Artificial Rainfall Alleviates Drought in Ningxia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- With the help of the air force
of Guangzhou Military Area Command of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army, Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region successfully
launched a massive artificial rainfall program in the arid
southern part of the region recently.
</P>
<P>
After a plane sprayed silver iodide acetone on thick cloud
layers, rain fell in Xihaigu around the Liupan Mountain. Yinchuan,
the regional capital which had received no rain for more than 150
days, also had a heavy shower.
</P>
<P>
A meteorologist estimated that 10,000 sq. km of area in Ningxia
had received an average precipitation of 10 mm. of rainfall. It
will benefit the growth of maize, oil-bearing crops and potatoes.
</P>
<P>
Some 1 million Muslims live in the southern part of Ningxia. An
unusually long dry spell, which lasted for three seasons since
last September, withered up winter wheat on large tracts of land
and created a shortage of drinking water for both local residents
and livestock.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
