<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0269 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: ABCs of Macao SAR Basic Law (56) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Will the international agreements that China has signed be
applicable to the MSAR?
</P>
<P>
There are specific provisions in Article 138 of the Basic Law
regarding this issue.
</P>
<P>
The Central People's Government will decide whether any
international agreement that the People's Republic of China has
signed or is a party to should apply to the MSAR in accordance
with the circumstances and needs of the Region and after seeking
the views of the Government of the Region.
</P>
<P>
It is clear from this Article that the power to decide on this
matter rests with the Central People's Government. The Central
Government shall base its decision on its judgment on the
applicability of the agreement after assessing and analyzing the
social system of the MSAR in line with the policy of "one country,
two systems".
</P>
<P>
In terms of procedure, the Central People's Government will
seek the opinions of the Government of the MSAR before making any
decision on this matter. In a word, the applicability of the
international agreements that China has signed to the MSAR depends
on the actual conditions and circumstances.
</P>
<P>
This is an expression of respect for the high degree of
autonomy enjoyed by the MSAR.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0270 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 07:17 </DATE_TIME>
