<HEADLINE> Boeing Business Jet Makes Longest Ever NonstopFlight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGLES, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A derivative of the Boeing
Next-Generation 737-700 has completed the longest ever nonstop
flight, the Boeing Company said ON Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Boeing Business Jet (BBJ) flew 13 hours 51 minutes and
traveled 11,580 kilometers. Taking off from Baltimore in eastern U.
S. last Friday, the airplane turned to the northeast state of
Maine, and then the West Coast cities of Seattle and San Diego,
Miami in the southeastern coast and finally back in Baltimore.
</P>
<P>
Average speed for the flight was 830 km per hour and almost 30
tons of fuel was used. With strengthened wings and landing gear,
the airplane was equipped with a nine-tank fuel system, giving the
BBJ to total fuel capacity of more than 40,000 liters.
</P>
<P>
Boeing Business Jet is a joint venture between the Boeing
Company and General Electric Company. Started in 1996, the venture
had received 46 BBJ orders. 
</P>
