<HEADLINE> Science Sharpens Competitive Edge in Petrochemical Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Science and technology has given
China's petrochemical industry a boost, with some 60 percent of 3,
000 scientific research findings being adopted throughout the
industry over the past ten years.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang Jiaren, vice-president of the China National
Petrochemical Corp. (Sinopec), through vigorous development in the
1980s and 1990s, China has set up a comprehensive petrochemical
processing system and established a group of backbone enterprises,
with annual refining capacity hitting 150 million tons, making it
third in oil refining capacity in the world.
</P>
<P>
The official said that China can now produce 80 percent of the
six types of catalysts which are vital to petrochemical production,
allowing it to save 200 million US dollars annually and cut
production costs by one billion yuan a year, said the official.
And 80 percent of the scientific findings on refining have been
put into use.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, great breakthroughs have also been
made in scientific and technological cooperation with overseas
petrochemical companies. Projects on three large-scale joint
ventures co-funded with Switzerland, Germany and Hong Kong are
proceeding well to produce polypropylene and polystyrene products.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a large group of important scientific research
joint ventures are under negotiation with overseas petrochemical
companies, he added. 
</P>
