<HEADLINE> Vietnam Prepares For '99 Kunming World Horticulture Exposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has planned to showcase the
beauty of its traditional family gardens at the '99 Kunming World
Horticulture Exposition which will run in Kunming, capital of
Yunnan Province in southwest China, from May 1 to October 31 this
year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's exhibit will reflect the close connection between the
Vietnamese and nature, according to a report of Vietnam's English
daily Vietnam News on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese experts will run a display called "Family Gardens of
the Vietnamese Wet Rice Civilization" at the World Horticulture
Exposition.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's 1,000 square meter exhibit will provide a glimpse of
typical Vietnamese horticulture, which is compatible with the
rural culture of the past, present and future.
</P>
<P>
The centerpiece will be a house surrounded by more than 500
square meters of fruit trees, a fish pond and a garden of
ornamental plants, flowers and stone landscaping.
</P>
<P>
The display will also provide a look at the Garden, Fish Pond
and Pigsty model, and enclosed biological system in which natural
sources such as soil, water, air and sunlight are used to protect
the environment.
</P>
<P>
Chinese government invited Vietnam to participate in the '99
Kunming World Horticulture Exposition during Vietnamese Prime
Minister Phan Van Khai's visit to China last year.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese Horticulturists' Association and the Vietnam
Natural and Traditional Beauty Association are in charge of
preparing for the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam News quoted the members of these organizations as
saying that they want to make the event success so that Vietnam
can strengthen its solidarity and friendship with China and other
participating countries.  
