<HEADLINE> Norwegian Parliament Approves Entry to EU Schengen Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The Norwegian parliament on
Monday approved the country's joining of the Schengen Accord,
which will open the borders between Norway and European Union
states.
</P>
<P>
Norway and the EU reached an agreement last year on its entry
to Schengen Accord, but the details and the date of effect remain
undecided until after consultations with other Nordic countries,
who are members of the EU.
</P>
<P>
Three Nordic countries, Denmark, Sweden and Finland, have not
joined the Schengen Accord because they have already realized the
free flow of citizens. Iceland reportedly agreed to participate in
the accord earlier.
</P>
<P>
Norway's approval has paved the way for an immediate joint
participation in the accord by all Nordic countries. 
</P>
