</P>
<P>
According to Susi, the baby was not supposed to be born yet but
fears that the situation would get worse prior to the June 7
general election prompted her to make the decision to give birth
early.
</P>
<P>
"I was supposed to give birth on May 11. But I'm worried that
the situation might be tense next month, so I decided to give
birth today (Monday she was quoted by national newspapers Tuesday
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on his first child, Budikusuma expressed hope that
the baby would bring peace to the world.
</P>
<P>
"I can say that my first daughter is a child of peace because
the name we gave her -- Laurencia Averina Wiratama -- means peace',
" Budikusuma said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
