<HEADLINE> Sacramento's Chris Webber Named Player of the Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Chris Webber of the Sacramento
Kings was today named NBA Player of the Week for games played
Monday, April 19, through Sunday, April 25.
</P>
<P>
Webber led the Kings to a 4-0 record by averaging 20.5 points,
11.8 rebounds, 3.0 assists, 2.00 steals and 1.50 blocked shots per
game. He shot .513 from the field, and ranked third in rebounding
and 16th in scoring among league leaders for the week.
</P>
<P>
Webber, who leads the NBA in rebounding with 13.0 per game,
began the week with 22 points, six rebounds, two assists and one
steal in a 102-98 win at the Los Angeles Clippers on Monday. He
had a team-high 25 points, 16 rebounds, five assists, five blocked
shots and three steals in a 103-94 defeat of Golden State on
Wednesday, and had 18 points, a game-high 19 rebounds, four
assists, and three steals in 105-97 victory over Minnesota on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Despite missing most of the second half due to lower back
spasms, Webber closed the week with 17 points, six rebounds and
one assist in a 105-102 defeat of Dallas on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA Player of the Week were Atlanta's
Dikembe Mutombo, Dallas' Michael Finley, the L.A. Clippers'
Maurice Taylor, Miami's Alonzo Mourning and Milwaukee's Glenn
Robinson. 
</P>
