<HEADLINE> Helicopter Maintenance Soldier Commended by PLA (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Li Hongtao, a soldier turned
helicopter maintenance expert has been honored by the Headquarters
of the General Staff of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) for his
outstanding achievements in military training.
</P>
<P>
He was cited as a modal soldier in the new era for learning and
mastering science and technology in a bid to guide his daily work.
Other PLA soldiers are asked to learn from him.
</P>
<P>
The young soldier of an airman regiment, who is a high school
graduate with only five years military service, has become the
first soldier to win the honorary title in the application of
science and technology in military training since the founding of
new China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
Having undertaken 18 specialized courses in higher-education in
such topics as the construction of helicopters, mechanical drawing
and the dynamics of flying, all self-taught, Li, who has been a
member of the army aviation squad in charge of helicopter
maintenance since December, 1994, has participated in more than 20
major helicopter related innovation projects.
</P>
<P>
Applying his self taught knowledge he has been involved in
tackling a series of problems such as increasing speed with which
large weapons can be moved from one place and preventing the tail
propeller from colliding with the ground.
</P>
<P>
Li is the first soldier to have a special paper published in
the state-level "Aviation Maintenance" magazine and the first
invited to an annual meeting of Chinese leading helicopter experts
in 1996 to present and read his paper "Proposals for Prevention of
Tail Propellers From Colliding With the Ground."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
