<HEADLINE> Shanghai Industry Grows 11.3 Percent In First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua)-- Shanghai, China's economic and
financial center, completed an industrial output value of 133.5
billion yuan in the first quarter, up 11.3 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The municipality's statistics bureau said that the industry
contributed 45.3 percent of its GDP and that the growth rate is an
increase of around 14 percentage points over that for the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's industrial economic efficiency has led the whole
country for nearly ten years, said the bureau.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed Shanghai's industrial boom to its
successful upgrading of its industrial structure, with a focus on
such sectors as autos, power plants, telecommunications and
household electrical appliances.
</P>
<P>
These new sectors now generate over half of the city's profits.
</P>
