<HEADLINE> Colibri Helicopter Fuselages Mass Produced in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Harbin Aircraft Manufacturing
Corporation (HAMC) in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province has
started mass production of fuselages for Colibri Helicopters,
considered the world's most advanced craft of their type..
</P>
<P>
With its production line almost fully expanded the corporation
says producing one fuselage every three days and by the end of
last week its total output had reached 60 since it began
operations in 1997.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 of the fuselages have been delivered to France for
assemblage.
</P>
<P>
Known as the Colibri, the EC120 helicopter is a joint
development involving a tripartite cooperation the HAMC, Singapore
Technologies Aerospace, and a French firm.
</P>
<P>
The French part of the operation is responsible for dynamics
and the hoist systems as well as providing general technological
support while the Chinese partner is responsible for manufacturing
the fuselages with the Singaporean company in charge of the tail
structure.
</P>
<P>
Chinese technical workers have participated in all the jobs
involving Colibri helicopters, including designing, producing,
obtaining the certificate of air worthiness marketing and after-
sale services.
</P>
<P>
Due to HAMC's outstanding job, the Singapore company decided to
transfer its task of producing other parts of the helicopter like
cabin doors to the Chinese company.
</P>
<P>
The Colibri is a five-seater, 1.5-ton helicopter and the first
customer was Nozaki of Japan, based in France. The helicopters
have won certificates of air worthiness in 19 countries including
the United States since their successful maiden flights in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Orders for about 200 Colibri helicopters have been placed and
at HAMC, the production plan goes well beyond the year of 2001,
said a HAMC spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
HAMC has so far earned 25 million yuan from the exports of the
Colibri helicopter fuselages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
