<HEADLINE> UNICEF Aid Project Implemented in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- An aid project supported by the
United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) to improve health
conditions in east China's Jiangxi Province has been accomplished
as scheduled with more than 700,000 flood victims benefiting.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi was one of the Chinese provinces hit hardest by last
summer's flooding on the Yangtze River. At least 260 waterworks,
173,000 pump wells and other facilities were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
UNICEF offered the province 800,000 U.S. dollars in aid mainly
to try and restore water supply facilities and disease prevention.
</P>
<P>
The funds has been used to repair 70 waterworks, replace 5,000
damaged pumps, and carry out a health education program in six
cities and counties.  
</P>
</TEXT>
