<HEADLINE> Source of Hong Kong's Drinking Water Protected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province
has just launched a new campaign to afforest the Sanbai Mountains,
where the Dongjiang River, which supplies drinking water to Hong
Kong, originates.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 volunteers from the province will plant over
100 hectares of maples around the river source during the next two
years.
</P>
<P>
Young people are especially encouraged to grow a "youth forest"
and "coming-of-age commemorative trees" around the mountain area.
</P>
<P>
Local enterprises and individuals are donating funds and goods
for the effort.
</P>
<P>
Anyuan County, where Sanbai is located, started to afforest the
mountain ten years ago. The Sanbai Natural Reserve has been
enlarged from 330 sq km to 800 sq km to better protect the river
source.  
</P>
</TEXT>
