<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets up Polar Educational Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
industrial and commercial city, has just established a polar
educational center to spread the knowledge about the South and
North Poles among the public.
</P>
<P>
The center, jointly set up by the Shanghai-based China Polar
Research Institute and a local neighborhood committee, consists of
a model of the earth and its polar extremes, an exhibition room
and a popular science hall.
</P>
<P>
The 500 sq m model is a plane granite design of the earth, and
marked on it are the poles, the Tropic of Capricorn, the Tropic of
Cancer, the international date line, and the route taken by
China's expeditions to the Antarctic.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition room and the popular science hall are full of
pictures and various samples from the two poles.
</P>
<P>
China has made 15 scientific expeditions to the South Pole and
will embark on the 16th later this year.
</P>
<P>
This year's expedition will mark the 15th anniversary of
China's maiden scientific voyage to the South Pole, as well as the
10th anniversary of the establishment of the Zhongshan Station
there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
