<HEADLINE> Defending Champion Enqvist Falls in Munich </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MUNICH, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Thomas Enqvist of
Sweden suffered an surprise 6-3, 3-6, 6-3 defeat to Romanian Dinu
Pescariu in the first round of Munich Open here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Holder Enqvist, ranked 17th in the world, was never in the
fight against the world No. 94 Romanian whom he beat in the first
round in the French Open last May.
</P>
<P>
Boris Becker is entered in his hometown tournament and starts
against sixth seed Wayne Ferreira on Tuesday. The German has a 9-1
record in that series.
</P>
<P>
Becker and fellow German Tommy Haas won a doubles match Monday,
Becker's first competition since his father died a week ago,
forcing him to pull out of the Monte Carlo Open.
</P>
<P>
Monte Carlo champion Gustavo Kuerten, the third seed behind
Karol Kucera of Slovakia and Enqvist, starts in Munich Tuesday
with a match against Italian Vicenzo Santopadre, 108th in the
world.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Alberto Berasatagui knocked out No. 6 seed Marc Rosset
of Switzerland 2-6, 6-3, 6-1 while Frenchman Arnaud Clement beat
seventh seed Jan Siemerink of the Netherlands 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
