<HEADLINE> French Judoka Stripped of Silver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Djamel Bouras of France, silver
medalist in the 78kg class at the 1997 World Judo Championships in
Paris, has been stripped of his medal by the International Judo
Federation, reports said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Francois Besson, sporting director of the body, said the
decision was made after Bouras was handed a 15-month ban after
testing positive for nandrolone on October 2, 1997 just a week
before winning the medal. 
</P>
