<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT April 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The United Nations Special Committee on
Peacekeeping concluded its 1999 session on Monday, stressing that
the primary responsibility for the maintenance of peace and
security rested with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The Committee also stressed that peacekeeping continued to be
one of the key instruments available to the Organization for
discharging that responsibility. (UN-Session)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- President Bill Clinton Monday called for a three-
day summit meeting with Israeli and Palestinian leaders within six
months after Israel holds election in May to complete the land-for-
security deal he helped bring about last October.
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Joe Lockhart issued the call for both
sides to work out a framework to revive peace talks running
aground late last year because of Israel's refusal to withdraw
from more part of the West Bank, stipulated by the Wye accord
approved last October by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat under the brokerage of
President Clinton. (Clinton-Israel-Palestinians)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS-- Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic is ready to allow
the International Committee of Red Cross (ICRC) to work in Kosovo,
said ICRC president Cornelio Sommaruga on Monday.
</P>
<P>
During an interview with the French television channel France 2,
Sommaruga said: "Milosevic has promised that we could go there
immediately, but I am expecting that be clarified in written form,
" said Sommaruga, who has just met with Milosevic in Belgrade. (
Milosevic-Red Cross-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- Albanian President Rexhep Meidani Monday called on
NATO to impose conditions on Yugoslavia to allow the Kosovo
refugees to return home, "including by using force."
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the French television channel France 2,
Meidani said: "The democratic countries should impose conditions
to make it possible the return of refugees to their homes,
including by using force." (Albania-NATO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- A unilateral Palestinian declaration of
statehood on May 4, 1999, would not only be "an unlawful" action,
but would undermine the framework capable of changing the
situation of the Palestinian people, Israel said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the United Nations, Israeli representative to
the United Nations Dore Gold rejected Palestinian arguments that a
transitional period would end on May 4, 1999. (Israel-Palestine
State)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Romania has granted so far the status of refugees
to 178 ethnic Serbians and Albanians coming in from neighboring
Yugoslavia, the national Rompres news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The refugees were boarded in the western counties of Arad,
Mehedinti and Timis, as well as in the central counties of Sibiu
and Brasov and in the capital city of Bucharest. (Romania-
Yugoslavia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON-- A U.S. Army Apache attack helicopter crashed on a
training mission in northern Albania Monday night, the U.S.
European Command said.
</P>
<P>
A statement by the Command reaching here from Germany said that
the two crewmen escaped and were in good condition. The cause of
the crash is under investigation. (Apache-Crash). 
</P>
