<HEADLINE> Foreign Investments on Indonesia's Agribusiness Double </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Although the total foreign direct
investments (PMA) in Indonesia last year dropped by 70 percent, in
fact the value of PMA in agribusiness doubled to 998.5 million
U.S. dollars last year from 465.3 million U.S. dollars a year
before.
</P>
<P>
State Minister for Investment Hamzah Haz, who is also chairman
of the National Coordinating Board of Investment, said the figures
were an indication that the agricultural sector could lead to
recovery from the crisis.
</P>
<P>
"When the other sectors experienced contraction up to 15.4
percent last year, agriculture grew by 0.3 percent," he was quoted
by The Indonesian Observer Tuesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said that the number of agribusiness projects also sharply
increased from only 14 to 134 projects.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that the mistake made by Indonesia "is not
paying much attention to developing agriculture which most of the
population depend on. If we could boost the growth of the sector
by nurturing the 39 million small- and medium-scale enterprises
intensively, our budget surplus will really come from trade not
from capital inflow anymore."
</P>
<P>
The economic crisis has brought a new blessing for the sector
to become the pillar to get out of the crisis, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990427.0359 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest State Farm Plays Big Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Xinjiang Production and
Construction Corporation, China's largest state farm, is playing
an important role in invigorating local economy.
</P>
<P>
The corporation, located in the northwestern Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region, is the country's largest enterprise in
agriculture, industry, commerce and trade.
</P>
<P>
In 1998 its output value totaled 16.35 billion yuan, up 10.3
percent from the previous year and its gross domestic product
reached 68.25 million yuan, an increase of 10.4 percent over 1997,
with annual average per capita income standing at 5,600 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The corporation's import and export volume reached 286 million
US dollars last year despite the Southeast Asian financial crisis,
100 times that of 1985, registering an annual increase rate of 42.
8 percent.
</P>
<P>
So far, it has forged economic and trade ties with 66 countries
and regions and set up 42 foreign-funded enterprises. And the
number of foreign-funded projects now numbers more than 100, with
actual use of foreign investment totaling 162 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Since its founding in 1954, the corporation has also
established 12 higher learning colleges, 172 farms and over 5,000
enterprises. It has reclaimed 960,000 ha of land and built a batch
of new towns.
</P>
<P>
Now its output of grain and sugar crop rank first in the
country along with its cotton output. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
