<HEADLINE> China Unicom to Increase Market Share </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- China United Telecommunications
Corp. (China Unicom), China Telecom's chief rival, will expand its
business this year as new investment measures are applied.
</P>
<P>
A new financing mode was introduced by China Unicom yesterday
when a frame agreement was signed for equipment purchase from
Ericsson, today's China Daily said.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, Ericsson will supply systems of
mobile telecommunications (GSM), accessories, and corresponding
system software.
</P>
<P>
China Unicom has three years to pay for the equipment and
payments will depend on the number of subscribers to the new
system.
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is an aggressive one and that is to amplify our
business this year, driven by a favorable operating climate
created by the government and the market," China Daily quoted Wand
Jianzhou, executive vice-president of China Unicom as saying.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
