<HEADLINE>   O'Sullivan and Williams Reach Final Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Ronnie O'Sullivan and Mark
Williams advanced into the top eight with clearcut second round
victories at the World Snooker Championships in Sheffield, England
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
World number three O'Sullivan beat English compatriot Joe Perry
13-8 and Welshman Williams defeated Nick Walker 13-7.
</P>
<P>
O'Sullivan appeared relaxed after his win, in stark contrast to
his mood last week when, after beating Leo Fernandez in the first
round, he hinted at possible retirement from the game.
</P>
<P>
"I've got most of my troubles out of the way now and I'm a lot
happier with my form," O'Sullivan said.
</P>
<P>
He forecast a tough match in the quarter-finals against John
Parrott.
</P>
<P>
"I haven't got the best of records against John," O'Sullivan
said. "He always seems to play well against me."
</P>
<P>
O'Sullivan was beaten by eventual champion John Higgins in the
semifinals last year.
</P>
<P>
Williams goes into his quarter-final against Ken Doherty, last
year's runner-up, in confident mood after collecting three titles
this season.
</P>
<P>
"I've won just as many tournaments as John Higgins this year
and if I can get past Ken, I fancy beating him," Williams said.
</P>
