<HEADLINE> BAR Calls Salo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The British American Racing team
have confirmed that Mika Salo will take the place of the injured
Ricardo Zonta at the San Marino Grand Prix next Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The veteran Finnish driver, 32, who has previously driven for
Lotus, Tyrrell and Arrows, will stand in for the Brazilian who
suffered a cut tendon in his left foot during a crash at his home
Grand Prix two weeks ago, according to local reports on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Zonta is recovering well but medical advisors have advised
against putting any undue strain on his foot for the next few days.
</P>
<P>
BAR felt the demanding Imola circuit could aggravate Zonta's
injury. The team's managing director Craig Pollock said: "It is a
great shame that Ricardo will not be able to drive for us at Imola,
and obviously a big disappointment for him personally.
</P>
<P>
"He agrees though that the quickest way back into the cockpit
is to allow his foot adequate time to heal fully and not rush his
return. In that respect he will be guided by the advice of his
doctors.
</P>
<P>
"In the meantime, we're pleased to have secured the services of
Mika Salo for Imola. He's a great driver and has current Formula
One experience."
</P>
<P>
Salo is looking forward to the chance to get behind the wheel
in Formula One for the first time in 1999 after being replaced at
Arrows.
</P>
<P>
He drove for BAR in testing at Jerez last week and said: "I'm
sorry that Ricardo won't be able to drive at Imola, but speaking
personally, I am very pleased to be able to step in to what I am
sure is a competitive car." 
</P>
